    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "EXAMPLE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "narration_text": "A classic helium calculation illustrates the direction of error: a compact trial family produced an energy near minus seventy-seven-point-five electron-volts, above the measured ground energy near minus seventy-eight-point-nine-eight. The useful word is above.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 14.91,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "What in the mathematics makes the error one-sided rather than merely small?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 4.69,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE DECOMPOSITION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "For a discrete spectrum, expand the normalized trial state in exact energy eigenstates. The same idea extends through the spectral theorem when continua are present.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.52,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE AVERAGE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Its expectation value is the sum of each energy times the squared magnitude of its coefficient. Those weights are nonnegative and, by normalization, sum to one.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.05,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE KEY STEP",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Every energy in the spectrum is at least the ground energy, or more generally at least the spectral infimum. Replace every energy in the average by that lower bound and the sum can only decrease.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.37,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE FLOOR",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Because the weights sum to one, the result is immediate: the trial expectation is greater than or equal to E zero.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "collapse"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.0,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "EQUALITY",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Equality occurs only when the trial state has support entirely in the ground eigenspace. With a unique ground state, that means the trial vector is the ground state up to an overall phase.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reveal"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.09,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE METHOD",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Now choose a parameterized trial family and minimize its expectation. The minimum is the best upper bound available inside that family, not necessarily the exact energy.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "scan"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.99,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE GUARANTEE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "The floor is E zero. A valid variational estimate may approach it or equal it, but cannot cross it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.57,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "ASSUMPTIONS",
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "narration_text": "The guarantee has conditions: normalize the trial state, keep it in the operator or quadratic-form domain, use the same self-adjoint Hamiltonian, and require that Hamiltonian to be bounded below. Violate those, and a suspicious low number diagnoses the setup, not the theorem.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "audit"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 16.49,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "act": "YOUR TURN",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Your turn. A normalized trial state has seventy percent weight on E zero and thirty percent on E one, where E one equals E zero plus two electron-volts. How far above E zero is its expectation?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.35,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B12.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T19:56:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "act": "YOUR TURN ANSWER",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Multiply the excitation gap by its weight: zero-point-three times two electron-volts is zero-point-six electron-volts. The ground-state weight contributes no excess above E zero.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reveal"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B13.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.46,
